short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Tries to open the current tab url in the Go Lang package documentation, i.e. pkg.go.dev

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Sometimes when you browse some Github repo written in Go you may want to go to it's official documentation. Sadly, sometimes the direct link to it is not presented in the repository main, hence you need to go and search for it... With go2docs you just click and a new tab with a query to the pkg.go.dev page is done, which will eventually resolve to the correct documentation if its a match!

Source code on Github: https://github.com/tarasyarema/go2docs
